The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning framework for open knowledge graph reasoning, which involves both natural language processing and graph reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves collaborative policy learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with filtering out irrelevant facts, which is related to information retrieval, falling under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with reasoning over a graph, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases).
